          },
          {
            "element_id": "33455555",
            "value": "Qingyue continues to request to use the translator to assist with comprehension of oral dialogue and to complete written assignments. She has made nice progress with identifying letters of the alphabet and sounds. She is improving in her ability to blend sounds into words. Qingyue now works 1-1 with the ELD teacher targeting conversation skills as well as ELD group instruction in listening, speaking, reading and writing. Qingyue successfully completed WIDA ACCESS testing in January and February. Results will be sent home in the Spring of 2026."
          },
          {
            "element_id": "33455558",
            "value": "Qingyue is making progress with her confidence in communicating with both peers and adults since the start of the school year. She is using Google Translate to assist with completing oral and written assignments. Qingyue is making friends and seems to enjoy interacting with peers during unstructured activities. She is a good helper when working with younger students."
